{"cursor":"4577","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Paul Saladin Leonhardt' (November 13, 1877 – December 14, 1934) was a\nGerman chess master.\n\nHe was born in Posen, Province of Posen, Poland (then German Empire), and died\nof a heart attack in KÃ¶nigsberg (East Prussia) during a game of chess.\n\nA player with a low profile and not many tournament wins, Leonhardt has been\nlargely forgotten by the history books. However, at his best, he was able to\ndefeat most of the elite players of the period. Tarrasch, Tartakower,\nNimzowitsch, MarÃ³czy and RÃ©ti all succumbed to his fierce attacking style\nbetween 1903 and 1920. He won several brilliancy prizes.\n\nIn major tournaments he was first at Hilversum 1903, Hamburg 1905, and\nCopenhagen 1907 (ahead of MarÃ³czy and Schlechter), making him Nordic Champion;\nthird, behind Rubinstein and MarÃ³czy, at Carlsbad 1907; second, behind Milan\nVidmar, at GÃ¶teborg 1909 (7th Nordic-ch), second, behind Rudolf Spielmann, at\nStockholm 1909, and second, behind Carl Ahues, at Duisburg (DSB Congress)\n1929. [http://www.anders.thulin.name/SUBJECTS/CHESS/CTCIndex.pdf Name\nIndex to Jeremy Gaige's Chess Tournament Crosstables ]\n\nIn matches he drew with Rudolf Loman (+4 â4 =2), won against James Mortimer (+5\nâ0 =3), defeated Samuel Passmore (6 : 2), and drew with Georg Schories (2 : 2)\nat London 1904, defeated Hector William Shoosmith (+5 â0 =1) at London 1905,\nlost to Jacques Mieses (+1 â5 =1) at London 1905, lost to Spielmann at Munich\n1906 (+4 â6 =5), lost to Frank Marshall (+1 â2 =4) at Hamburg 1911, defeated\nNimzowitsch (+4 â0 =1) at Hamburg 1911, lost to Hugo SÃ¼chting (1.5 : 2.5) at\nHamburg 1911 and drew with him (2 : 2) at Hamburg 1912, won against Moishe\nLowtzky (+5 â1 =1) at Leipzig 1913, * drew with Hans Fahrni (1 : 1),\nwon against Jeno Szekely (2.5 : 1.5), both at Munich 1914, and drew with Curt\nvon Bardeleben (2 : 2) at Berlin\n1921. [http://www.thechesslibrary.com/files/ShortMatchesOf20thCentury.htm\nShort Matches of the 20th Century ]\n\nAs an expert analyst of the openings, he wrote a monograph on the Ruy Lopez\n(Zur Spanische Partie - 1913). Opening variations have been attributed to him\nin the Lopez, Sicilian Defence, Ponziani Opening, Evans Gambit, and the\nScandinavian Defense.\n","linknr":161,"url":"Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt","recorded":1374767848,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt.jpg/170px-Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt.jpg","/wiki/File:Paul_Saladin_Leonhardt.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf7/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/Germans","/wiki/Chess","/wiki/Pozna%C5%84","/wiki/Province_of_Posen","/wiki/K%C3%B6nigsberg","/wiki/Siegbert_Tarrasch","/wiki/Savielly_Tartakower","/wiki/Aron_Nimzowitsch","/wiki/G%C3%A9za_Mar%C3%B3czy","/wiki/Richard_R%C3%A9ti","/wiki/Hilversum","/wiki/Hamburg","/wiki/Copenhagen","/wiki/Carl_Schlechter","/wiki/Nordic_Chess_Championship","/wiki/Akiba_Rubinstein","/wiki/Carlsbad_1907_chess_tournament","/wiki/